name: SCNetworkReachabilityContext
desc: Structure containing user-specified data and callbacks used with SCNetworkReachabilitySetCallback(_:_:_:).

items.name: copyDescription
items.desc: The callback used to provide a description of the info field.

items.name: info
items.desc: A C pointer to a user-specified block of data.

items.name: release
items.desc: The callback used to remove a retain previously added for the info field. If this parameter is not a pointer to a function of the correct prototype, the behavior is undefined. The value can be NULL.

items.name: retain
items.desc: The callback used to add a retain for the info field. If this parameter is not a pointer to a function of the correct prototype, the behavior is undefined. The value can be NULL.

items.name: version
items.desc: The version number of the structure type being passed in as a parameter to an SCDynamicStore creation function. This structure is version 0.
